{"product_id": "12170", "page": 10, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-03", "text": "GTA1 is a PC classic by now. The first two GTA games are both in a 2D top-down style. The gameplay resembles what you'd expect to find in any Grand Theft Auto game: steal cars, run down pedestrians, and evade the police. The difference is that this game offers very little else. There's a very loose mission structure, but really very little reason to care about them. This game truly is a sandbox, which can be fun to play around in, but the lack of direction prevents it from holding your attention for too long.\nThe graphics are decent for the time. The sound can get obnoxious quickly, and there's no music. The controls aren't very good, and I found it imposible to play with a controller.\nAt the very least, the price is right. You can't buy it individually on Steam, but it's free on Rockstar's website.", "hours": 0.0, "username": "UjuidarEhcram", "products": 1154, "early_access": false}
