{"product_id": "12170", "page": 12, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-02-19", "text": "The one that started it all - and I mean getting the editor of the Daily Mail to threaten to resign if the game wasn't banned. Four games later, the GTA series succeeded. Back to the original, witness (read: cause) such atrocities like 'Gouranga': achieved by running down lines of Hare Krishna monks. Beg, kill, steal, and cheat your way into avoiding cops to earn your cool million bucks. Then get out of town as fast as you can... crime just isn't what it used to be.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "PaulusMaximus1983", "products": 375, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12170", "page": 12, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-22", "text": "The controls on this game suck\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 but hey, it's FREE.  I tried this game with a controller thinking maybe it'd be better, only it got worse. Anyway, my recommendation for this game is to avoid it unless you're bored, have nostalgia goggles to go with it, or unless you've found some way to make the controls worth it, in which case, TELL ME.", "hours": 1.4, "username": "arleas", "products": 2113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12170", "page": 12, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-23", "text": "A controversial classic which flourished into something yet even MORE controversial.  Has a DOPE soundtrack that you will remember for years to come including all genres.  The best part is the country song, because the lyrics make fun of country songs!  WIN!", "username": "Rumjaku", "products": 1076, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12170", "page": 12, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-12", "text": "One awesome little game that started it all. It only has a top down view that takes a few mins to get adjusted to, but once you get the controls, it is a pretty cool little game. It still has all of the crazy and wackiness as the new ones, and you also have freedom to make money however you want in the city. The only thing is it has the old school like difficulty, and that might turn others off, but I still think this is an awesome game. You can also play it on anything, even a netbook.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "defiance5050", "products": 607, "early_access": false}
